india, it must be noted that people in eastern india (west bengal and assam) generally consume tea without spices, the english way. this is also the part of india where most tea is grown. in south india, coffee (especially sweet "filter coffee") replaces tea as a standard beverage. alcohol[edit] drinking alcohol can either be frowned upon or openly accepted, depending on the region and religion of the area within which you are drinking. for example, goa, punjab, and pondicherry tend to be more free-wheeling (and have low taxes on alcohol), while a few southern areas like chennai are less tolerant 